.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "February 2026" "hsh" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a minimal UNIX command interpreter.

It reads commands from standard input and executes them by creating a child
process using fork(2) and running the command using execve(2).

In interactive mode (when standard input is a terminal), the prompt
.B ($)
is displayed before each command.

In non-interactive mode, commands are read from standard input without a prompt.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
If the command contains a slash ("/"), it is executed directly as a path.
Otherwise,
.B hsh
searches for the command in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status is the exit status of the last executed command.
When a command is not found, the status is 127.
.SH ERRORS
Error messages match
.BR sh (1)
format, except the program name is taken from argv[0].

Example:
.br
./hsh: 1: qwerty: not found
